# Environment Variables for Vercel Deployment

## Google OAuth Authentication (REQUIRED)
# Create OAuth credentials at: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 1. Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application)
# 2. Add authorized redirect URI: https://your-domain.vercel.app/api/auth/google/callback
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret

## Supabase Database (REQUIRED)
# Create a free account at: https://supabase.com
# 1. Create a new project
# 2. Go to Settings → API to find these keys
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key

## Vercel (Auto-populated on Vercel)
# VERCEL_URL will be automatically set by Vercel platform
# No need to manually set this in your env vars

## Node Environment
NODE_ENV=production

# Local Development (.env.local)
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local for local testing
# 2. Update values with your actual credentials
# 3. For local development, VERCEL_URL defaults to http://localhost:3000
# 4. Add test users in Google Cloud Console if app is in development
